The paper discusses the integration of structured knowledge graphs with deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.KR), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically mentions the use of knowledge graphs for building explainable AI systems, which further supports the inclusion of cs.CL and cs.KR as likely categories.
